# VibeWarden Security Sidecar — Claude Code Instructions

## Security layer

This application runs behind **VibeWarden**, a security sidecar that handles all
security concerns as a separate process. VibeWarden listens on port 8080 and
forwards authenticated, rate-limited requests to this app on port {{ .UpstreamPort }}.

**Do not implement any of the following yourself — VibeWarden handles them:**
{{ if .AuthEnabled }}
### Authentication

Authentication is fully managed by VibeWarden via Ory Kratos. Every request that
reaches this app has already been authenticated.

Authenticated requests carry these headers — read them instead of implementing session logic:

| Header | Value |
|--------|-------|
| `X-User-Id` | Unique user identifier |
| `X-User-Email` | User's verified email address |
| `X-User-Verified` | `true` when the user's email is verified |

**To make a path publicly accessible (no auth required)**, add it to `vibewarden.yaml`:

```yaml
auth:
  public_paths:
    - "/your/public/path"
    - "/api/webhooks/*"
```
{{ end }}
{{ if .RateLimitEnabled }}
### Rate limiting

Rate limiting is configured at {{ .RateLimitRPS }} requests/second per client IP.
Do not implement your own rate limiting — duplicate limiting will cause incorrect
behaviour for legitimate users.

Requests that exceed the limit receive a `429 Too Many Requests` response before
they reach this app.
{{ end }}
{{ if .TLSEnabled }}
### TLS

TLS termination is handled by VibeWarden. This app receives plain HTTP on
port {{ .UpstreamPort }}. Do not configure TLS in the app itself.
{{ end }}
### Security headers

VibeWarden injects the following security headers on every response:

- `Strict-Transport-Security` (HSTS)
- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`
- `X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN`
- `Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'`
- `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`

Do not set these headers in application code — they will conflict or be duplicated.

## VibeWarden endpoints

These endpoints are served by VibeWarden at the sidecar address (port 8080):

| Endpoint | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `GET /_vibewarden/health` | Health check — returns `200 OK` with JSON status |
{{ if .AdminEnabled }}| `/_vibewarden/admin/*` | Admin API — requires `X-Admin-Key` header |{{ end }}

Use `/_vibewarden/health` as the liveness probe in Docker Compose or Kubernetes.

## Configuration reference

VibeWarden is configured in `vibewarden.yaml` at the project root. Key sections:
{{ if .AuthEnabled }}
- `auth.public_paths` — paths that bypass authentication
- `kratos.public_url` — Ory Kratos public API URL
{{ end }}
{{ if .RateLimitEnabled }}
- `rate_limit.per_ip.requests_per_second` — per-IP rate limit
- `rate_limit.exempt_paths` — paths that bypass rate limiting
{{ end }}
Full reference: https://vibewarden.dev/docs/config
